Name: systemWindowColor

Type: property

Syntax: get the systemWindowColor

Summary:
Returns the current system window background color as a hex string.

Introduced: 9.6

OS: mac

Platforms: desktop

Example:
set the backgroundColor of this stack to the systemWindowColor

Description:
The <systemWindowColor> property returns the resolved window background color for
the current system appearance as a hex color string in the form "#rrggbb". This
reflects the actual color used by the OS for window backgrounds, taking dark mode
into account.

On Mac Apple Silicon (arm64) the value updates whenever the system appearance
changes and corresponds to NSColor's windowBackgroundColor resolved in the
effective appearance. On all other platforms and operating systems the property
returns empty.

Use this property together with <systemAppearance> to style controls so they
blend with the native window background.

References: systemAppearance (property), systemAppearanceChanged (message)
